author: MrElculver2424
description:
Relax, "drift away", and enjoy! Don't forget to comment, rate and share :)

I like to make a whole video to go along with songs. The reason I always do that for my videos is because I know a lot of people who feel better and enjoy the song more when they watch pictures and a video with it, rather than just one picture through the whole song. I hope you all enjoy this and my other videos too!

Mentor Williams wrote the song "Drift Away" and it was originally performed by John Henry Kurtz in his 1972 album "Reunion". Dobie Gray did this song in 1973 and his is the most popular version. Uncle Kracker then performed this in 2003.

A friend of mine also did his own video of this original song, which was by Dobie Gray. Check his out:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JR1sz8lkDF4
